The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Shivika wins in Nigeria 
                                                   Shivika wins in Nigeria 
            A STAFF REPORTER                       
	Calcutta: City girl Shivika Burman won her first womens pro-circuit match in Benin, Nigeria, on Wednesday.         
	According to information received here, Shivika beat Nigerian wild card Fathima Abinu 6-0, 6-1.               
	Equestrian         
	The national equestrian competition, hosted by the Fort William Riding Institute, got underway on Wednesday. The meet was inaugurated by Major General A.M. Verma, SM, VSM, Bengal Area.                     
	BASKETBALL: Mercantile mixed meet at Rangers Club from 6.30 pm         
	EQUESTRIAN: Meet at Pat Williamson Grounds from 3pm.         
	TENNIS: ITF Futures at Jaidip Mukerjea Tennis Academy from 9am                                                                                                                       
